research/history/round_summaries/round_0151.json:54:      "\u8bc4\u4f30\u65f6\u5fc5\u987b\u540c\u65f6\u8bb0\u5f55 FVU\u3001tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u3001final_total_tokens\uff0c\u533a\u5206\u662f\u7ed3\u6784\u66f4\u7b80\u5355\u5e26\u6765\u7684\u541e\u5410\u63d0\u5347\uff0c\u8fd8\u662f\u786e\u6709\u66f4\u597d\u7684\u603b\u6210\u672c-\u8d28\u91cf\u6743\u8861\u3002"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0151.json:57:      "\u82e5 lowrank_residual \u5728\u663e\u8457\u66f4\u4f4e selection_cost \u4e0e deploy \u6210\u672c\u4e0b\u4ec5\u5c0f\u5e45\u635f\u5931 FVU\uff0c\u5219\u8bf4\u660e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684\u590d\u6742\u7ed3\u6784\u4f18\u52bf\u4e0d\u8db3\u4ee5\u8986\u76d6\u5176\u603b\u6210\u672c\uff0c\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u6309\u89c4\u5219\u56de\u5230\u4e3b\u7ebf\u540e\u5e94\u8c28\u614e\u7ee7\u7eed\u6295\u5165\u8be5 family\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0151.json:58:      "\u82e5 lowrank_residual \u660e\u663e\u66f4\u5dee\uff0c\u5219\u8bf4\u660e\u4e0d\u4ec5\u7b2c\u4e8c\u9636\u6bb5 refinement \u6709\u4ef7\u503c\uff0csoft-codebook coarse branch \u672c\u8eab\u4e5f\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u5fc5\u8981\u7ed3\u6784\u6536\u76ca\uff0c\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u56de\u5230\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7ee7\u7eed\u505a\u4e3b\u7ebf recipe/\u6210\u672c\u5de5\u4f5c\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0151.json:79:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u6b21\u4e25\u683c matched architecture probe\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6362\u6210\u66f4\u7b80\u5355\u7684 lowrank_residual\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5168\u90e8\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u4e00\u8f6e\u5e72\u51c0\u5bf9\u7167\u5224\u65ad soft-codebook + two-stage \u7ed3\u6784\u76f8\u5bf9\u57fa\u7840 low-rank residual \u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_factorized_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:19:    "hypothesis": "`whitened_lowrank_residual` failed catastrophically at the matched K128 anchor, so the next matched architecture probe should avoid more whitening-style conditioning and instead test a different single-stage low-rank selector family. The most informative remaining probe is `lowrank_factorized_residual`: it preserves the low-rank trunk and static-library weighted-sum export path, but replaces the plain residual scorer with a factorized scorer. This answers one clean question: can a more structured single-stage selector recover enough of the two-stage mainline's quality to be worth continuing, or is the second residual stage itself the essential ingredient. If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants are likely not worth further follow-up in the current regime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_factorized_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_factorized_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. I am explicitly avoiding `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` because with the current batch-size-1 regime it collapses to ordinary top-k behavior and would not be an informative matched probe. The main risk is that `lowrank_factorized_residual` may add selector complexity without helping quality or LUTurbo online cost, so this should be judged strictly as a yes/no family-worthiness test before returning to the mainline.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:30:        "value": "lowrank_factorized_residual"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:51:      "Round 91 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:56:      "If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, treat the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants as low priority and resume mainline tuning next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0091.json:57:      "If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a structured single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."
